The state capture inquiry will resume on Monday. The commission will hear testimony from former Chief Director from the office of the Minister in the Presidency, Brent Adrian Simons. JOHANNESBURG - The state capture inquiry will resume on Monday. The commission will hear testimony from former Chief Director from the office of the Minister in the Presidency, Brent Adrian Simons. READ: A year on, Zondo reflects on state capture inquiry It will also hear testimony from former Chief of Staff at the Ministry in the Presidency and Ministry of Public Service and Administration, Abegnigo Hlungwani. It's been over a year since the inquiry began.